.content#tokens
  = render partial: 'shared/who'
  %h1 Two-Factor Authentication
  :markdown
    Two-factor authentication makes your account even more secure. It requires
    you to enter your username, your existing password, and a code from a
    TOTP-compatible app when logging in.

    ## Getting Started
    1. Install [Authy for iOS and Android](https://www.authy.com/thefuture#install-now) or
    [Google Authenticator for iOS, Android, and BlackBerry](https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/1066447?hl=en).
    2. Scan the QR code below into the app.
    3. Complete the form below.
    4. Print out the next screen and keep in a safe place.

  .qr
    %img{src: url_for(action: 'show', id: @temporary_secret, format: 'png'), width: 369, height: 369}

  %h2 Enable Two-Factor Authentication

  = form_tag token_path do
    %input{type: 'hidden', name: 'temporary_secret', value: @temporary_secret}
    %div.checkbox
      %input#i-promise{type: 'checkbox', name: 'i-promise'}
      %label{for: 'i-promise'}
        By enabling two-factor authentication I promise I won't forget my password,
        lose my token, or fail to keep my recovery tokens.
    %div
      %label{for: 'first-code'} Code from application
      %input#first-code{type: 'text', name: 'first-code', value: '', placeholder: 'Please promise to not lose your code above'}
    %div
      %label
      %input{type: 'submit', value: 'Enable Two-Factor'}
